'''Hai Inn Temple''' ({{zh|s=海印古寺}}), is a [[Buddhist]] monastery in [[Singapore]]. The present premises are located at [[Tengah
]], [[Singapore]].

==Overview==

'''Hai Inn Temple''' was founded in 1928 and is one of the oldest Buddhist temples in Singapore.<ref name="history">{{cite web | title = History of Haiinn Temple | publisher = Haiinn Temple (Singapore) | url = http://www.haiinn.org/content.php?grp=6 | accessdate = 2014-09-10}}</ref> Regular activities include dharma classes and monthly chanting sessions.<ref>{{cite journal|title=2006 April Activities|journal=For You Information|issue=204|accessdate=9 September 2014}}</ref> The temple has one of the biggest bells of its kind in Singapore, weighing 7 tonnes, with a height of 2.75 metres and 1.7 metres wide.<ref name="history" />

