{{Islam by country}}
'''Islam in the Cook Islands''' is a small religious minority in the [[New Zealand]] dependency of the [[Cook Islands]]. It's not exaclty clear how many Muslims are there in the Cook Islands, because the calculation of Muslims doesn't participate in the country census.<ref name=republika>{{cite web | url=http://www.republika.co.id/berita/dunia-islam/islam-mancanegara/13/03/04/mj406p-ranumnya-islam-di-cook-islands | title=Ranumnya Islam di Cook Islands | language=Indonesian | accessdate=August 13, 2017 }}</ref> However, it's estimated that about 0.06% of the Islands' population of about 15000 is Muslim.<ref>[http://www.ijesd.org/papers/30-D439.pdf Muslim population in Oceania: 1950-2020]</ref> But there are no mosques in the Islands. It's unclear how Islam first appeared in the Cook Islands.<ref name=republika></ref> One of the earliest few Cook Islanders to convert to Islam is [[Tatiana Kautai]].<ref>{{cite book|editor1-last=Crocombe|editor1-first=Ronald Gordon|title=Asia in the Pacific Islands: Replacing the West|date=2007|publisher=IPS publications |isbn=9789820203884|pages=374-375|url=https://books.google.co.ma/books?id=iDg9oAkwsXAC&pg=PA375&lpg=PA375&dq=tatiana+kautai+islam+in+cook+islands&source=bl&ots=LVD5IRGREh&sig=r1AqsRQiFOxsdxjnggN5C8cOXKw&hl=ar&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=tatiana%20kautai%20islam%20in%20cook%20islands&f=false|accessdate=August 13, 2017}}</ref> Currently, Islam is a small but growing religious minority in the Cook Islands.<ref name=republika></ref>
