'''Krantiveer Lahuji Raghoji Salve''' (14 November, 1800 – 17 February 1881), was an activist and social reformer from [[Purander, Maharashtra]]. Lahuji is also referred to as Lahujibuwa Mang, since he was from the Dalit [[Mang (caste)|Mang]] community. His father was Raghoji and mother Vithabai. 
[[Krantiveer Lahuji Salve]] worked for [[Chhatrapati shivaji maharaj|Shri Chhatrapati shivaji maharaj]]. Because of his great work shivaji maharaj honored him with name "Raut".

